ğŸ“– Usage
1. Open main.py (or your script name).
2. Update the my_target variable to your desired alert price.
3. Run the script:
  python main.py

ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture
The project follows a simple Request-Response cycle:
Input: User defines a target price.
Process: Script polls the CoinGecko API every 30 seconds.
Logic: Comparison operator checks if Current Price <= Target Price.
Output: Alert triggered in the terminal.

